@startuml scene-transition-lifecycle
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #f8f8f8
  BorderColor #333333
}

title Scene Transition Lifecycle (Pedagogical Intent Annotated)

[*] --> MainMenu : app start

state MainMenu
note right of MainMenu
Entry and mode selection.
Students choose sequential or collaborative path.
end note

state SPOptionsDialog : Singleplayer Options\n(popup Window)
note left of SPOptionsDialog
Configure card count, value range,
buffer size, and start game.
end note

state SinglePlayer
note right of SinglePlayer
Sequential baseline (T1).
Single student manipulates full card set.
end note

state MPOptionsDialog : Multiplayer Options\n(popup Window)
note left of MPOptionsDialog
Connect to GDSync, host or join lobby.
Enter room code or browse public lobbies.
end note

state MultiplayerLobby : Multiplayer Lobby\n(popup Window)
note right of MultiplayerLobby
Session setup and player discovery.
Host configures settings (buffer, cards, barrier mode).
Players join and appear in player list.
end note

state MultiplayerGame
note right of MultiplayerGame
OpenMP-style collaborative mode.
Shared container + private buffers + barrier sync.
end note

state Completion : Completion / Results
note right of Completion
Time/moves feedback.
Used for speedup and coordination discussion.
end note

MainMenu --> SPOptionsDialog : "Singleplayer" button\n(opens dialog)
SPOptionsDialog --> SinglePlayer : SceneManager.goto_scene()

MainMenu --> MPOptionsDialog : "Multiplayer" button\n(opens dialog)
MPOptionsDialog --> MultiplayerLobby : on lobby created/joined\n(opens lobby window)
MultiplayerLobby --> MultiplayerGame : host presses Start Game\n(GDSync broadcast to all clients)

SinglePlayer --> Completion : sorted && validated
MultiplayerGame --> Completion : globally sorted && synchronized

Completion --> MainMenu : return to menu / replay choice
SinglePlayer --> MainMenu : back action
MultiplayerLobby --> MainMenu : leave lobby / close window
MultiplayerGame --> MainMenu : exit / disconnect handling

@enduml

